            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>In the archonship of Artemidoros son of Eielos and Gnaios  son of Oppios, on the new moon of Panamos. Since the Ennaioi have always been well-disposed towards us, both when we were in our own land and when we were expelled from it and were wandering, encouraging us and receiving us in their city and territory; resolved by the council and the assembly that they are to enjoy good will and common citizenship with the people of Entella for all time. The archons are to write this decree on a bronze plaque and exhibit it in the council.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#JP">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>Tablet VIII (Nenci), was first published as tablet VII by Daux, and subsequently confused with a fake copy of the same. The bibliography is intended to cover principal editions only. For a recent historical discussion, elucidating the First Punic War context, see Lombardo, Mario. 2018. «Entella tra i Cartaginesi e i Romani, ovvero da chi erano stati espulsi gli Entellini». In Munus Laetitiae. Studi miscellanei offerti a Maria Letizia Lazzarini, a cura di Francesco Camia, Lavinio Del Monaco, e Michela Nocita, 2:485–98. Rome: Sapienza Universita Editrice; and Souza 2024.<ref target="https://doi.org/10.13133/9788893770736">https://doi.org/10.13133/9788893770736</ref>. See also Souza 2024.</p>
                </div>
